  <title translate="true">GHB: General-Head Boundary Package Pane</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">GHB: General-Head Boundary Package Pane</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">GHB: General-Head Boundary package</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> pane is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab of the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The data that can be specified for the Drain package are the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Starting time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ending time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Boundary Head</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Conductance</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">. &#160;The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Boundary Head</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> is the head of the external water body (or other feature) that is connected to the GHB cell. &#160;Water enters and leaves the cell containing the GHB cell at a rate of flow proportional to the difference between the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Boundary Head</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> and the head in the cell. &#160;The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Conductance</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> is the factor that relates the difference in head to the rate of flow. &#160;</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Starting time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Ending time</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> are explained in the help for the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">If parameters are used with an object, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Boundary Head</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> must be defined for each parameter as well as a multiplier for the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Conductance</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">. &#160;MODFLOW will multiply the multiplier by the parameter value (specified in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="GHB_General_Head_Boundary_Package" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Packages and Programs</link><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> dialog box) to determine the conductance to apply.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.0; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; tabstops:none;"><snippet src="Conductance_Interpretation"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.0; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">Of all the head-dependant flux boundaries, only the General-Head Boundary package has a linear relationship between head at the boundary and flux through the boundary. &#160;This linear characteristic is advantageous for automated calibration of models.</text></para>
  </body>
